Why you are not allowed to see other's IDs

If you go to the support tab, it literally says not to share your ID with anyone else.
In further details, inside PlayFab, every account gets a PlayFabId.

It’s not a password.
It’s not a secret key.
It’s an identifier.

It becomes a problem if someone:
Uses it to try unauthorized API calls
Spoofs requests
Automates abuse against other accounts
Uses it to track players, which violates privacy

All of these violate the ToS of Gorilla Tag which can be found at gorillatagvr.com/tos.
